-- Pemex’s Former CEO Ramirez Corzo Joins Oilfield Services Firm
-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 2012-02-28T00:32:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/pemex-s-former-ceo-ramirez-corzo-joins-oilfield-services-firm.html
Integradora de Servicios Petroleros
Oro Negro recruited Luis Ramirez Corzo, the former chief
executive officer of  Mexico ’s state oil company,  Petroleos
Mexicanos , as executive president.  Oro Negro “has secured $250 million in commitments” to
pursue oilfield service contracts in Mexico, the company said in
an e-mailed statement today.  Ramirez Corzo, 64, stepped down from the Mexico City-based
company known as Pemex in December of 2006. He will be joined at
Oro Negro by Gilberto Perezalonso and Gonzalo Gil White as co-
chief executive officers, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carlos Manuel Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
